<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,375,721]" pageId="1" pageNumber="55">
Notes:—Following the classification proposed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Field, A. R. &amp; Testo, W. &amp; Bostock, P. D. B. &amp; Holtum, J. A. M. &amp; Waycott, M." box="[624,800,483,505]" pageId="1" pageNumber="55" pagination="635 - 657" refId="ref1850" refString="Field, A. R., Testo, W., Bostock, P. D. B., Holtum, J. A. M. &amp; Waycott, M. (2016) Molecular phylogenetics and the morphology of the Lycopodiaceae subfamily Huperzioideae supports three genera: Huperzia, Phlegmariurus and Phylloglossum. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 94: 635 - 657. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. ympev. 2015.09.024" type="journal article" year="2016">
Field 
<emphasis box="[680,729,483,505]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="55">et al.</emphasis>
(2016)
</bibRefCitation>
and later retained by PPG 
<collectionCode box="[1063,1071,484,505]" country="Romania" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14415" name="&amp;quot;Alexandru Ioan Cuza&amp;quot; University" pageId="1" pageNumber="55" type="Herbarium">I</collectionCode>
(2016), this species formerly placed in 
<taxonomicName authority="Bernhardi (1801: 126)" authorityName="Bernhardi" authorityPageNumber="126" authorityYear="1801" box="[189,497,519,541]" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Lycopodiaceae" genus="Huperzia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lycopodiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="55" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[189,278,520,541]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="55">Huperzia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bernhardi, J. J." box="[284,497,519,541]" pageId="1" pageNumber="55" pagination="121 - 136" refId="ref1425" refString="Bernhardi, J. J. (1801) Tentamen alterum filices in genera redigenda. Journal fur die Botanik (Schrader) 1800: 121 - 136." type="journal article" year="1801">Bernhardi (1801: 126)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
belongs in 
<taxonomicName authority="Holub (1964: 21)" authorityName="Holub" authorityPageNumber="21" authorityYear="1964" box="[607,924,519,541]" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Lycopodiaceae" genus="Phlegmariurus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lycopodiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="55" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[607,751,519,540]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="55">Phlegmariurus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Holub, J." box="[756,924,519,541]" pageId="1" pageNumber="55" pagination="16 - 22" refId="ref2270" refString="Holub, J. (1964) Lycopodiella, novy rod radu Lycopodiales. Preslia 36: 16 - 22." type="journal article" year="1964">Holub (1964: 21)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. It is endemic to 
<collectingCountry box="[1085,1236,519,541]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="1" pageNumber="55">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
, but may possibly also occur in 
<collectingCountry box="[273,439,555,577]" name="French Polynesia" pageId="1" pageNumber="55">French Polynesia</collectingCountry>
according to recent observations (
<collectionCode box="[771,783,555,576]" country="South Africa" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14647" name="University of the Witwatersrand" pageId="1" pageNumber="55" type="Herbarium">J</collectionCode>
. Nitta, pers. com.).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,375,721]" pageId="1" pageNumber="55">
The 
<typeStatus box="[184,230,590,614]" pageId="1" pageNumber="55">type</typeStatus>
at 
<collectionCode box="[262,276,590,613]" country="France" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15763" name="Museum National d' Histoire Naturelle, Paris (MNHN) - Vascular Plants" pageId="1" pageNumber="55" type="Herbarium">P</collectionCode>
was determined in 2015 by 
<collectionCode box="[577,596,589,613]" country="USA" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15406" name="Harvard University - Arnold Arboretum" pageId="1" pageNumber="55" type="Herbarium">A</collectionCode>
. Field as 
<taxonomicName authority="(Brown 1810: 165) A. R. Field &amp; Bostock (2013: 49)" authorityName="A. R. Field &amp; Bostock" authorityPageNumber="49" authorityYear="2013" baseAuthorityName="Brown" baseAuthorityPageNumber="165" baseAuthorityYear="1810" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Lycopodiaceae" genus="Phlegmariurus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lycopodiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="55" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="varius">
<emphasis box="[699,933,589,613]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="55">Phlegmariurus varius</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Brown, R." box="[946,1136,589,613]" pageId="1" pageNumber="55" pagination="1802 - 1805" refId="ref1535" refString="Brown, R. (1810) Prodromus Florae Novae Hollandiae et Insulae van-Diemen, exhibens characteres plantarum quas annis 1802 - 1805 per oras utriusque insulae collegit et descripsit Robertus Brown; insertis passim aliis speciebus auctori hucusque cognitis, seu evulgatis, seu ineditis praesertim Banksianis, in primo itinere navarchi Cook detectis, 1. J. Johnson &amp; Co., London. 590 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 6720" type="book chapter" year="1810">Brown 1810: 165</bibRefCitation>
) A.R. 
<bibRefCitation author="Field, A. &amp; Bostock, P." pageId="1" pageNumber="55" pagination="33 - 51" refId="ref1789" refString="Field, A. &amp; Bostock, P. (2013) New and existing combinations in Palaeotropical Phlegmariurus (Lycopodiaceae) and lectotypification of the type species Phlegmariurus phlegmaria (L.) T. Sen &amp; U. Sen. PhytoKeys 20: 33 - 51. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / phytokeys. 20.4007" type="journal article" year="2013">Field &amp; Bostock (2013: 49)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
due to the lack of the combination 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rouhan &amp; A. R. Field" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Rouhan &amp; A. R. Field" baseAuthorityYear="2021" box="[568,738,625,649]" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Lycopodiaceae" genus="Phlegmariurus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lycopodiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="55" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pseudovarius">
<emphasis box="[568,738,625,649]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="55">P. pseudovarius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and because he thought it may be a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="A. R. Field &amp; Bostock" authorityYear="2013" baseAuthorityName="Brown" baseAuthorityYear="1810" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Lycopodiaceae" genus="Phlegmariurus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lycopodiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="55" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="varius">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="55">Phlegmariurus varius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. More recent work provides evidence supporting 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rouhan &amp; A. R. Field" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Rouhan &amp; A. R. Field" baseAuthorityYear="2021" box="[737,906,661,685]" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Lycopodiaceae" genus="Phlegmariurus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lycopodiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="55" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pseudovarius">
<emphasis box="[737,906,661,685]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="55">P. pseudovarius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as distinct, along with at least two other species in this complex (Field, unpublished data).
</paragraph>
